Israeli Army Targets Gaza, Hamas Rejects Ceasefire Proposal

### English Text Summary:
The Israeli army announced airstrikes on approximately 40 sites in Gaza, following Hamas's rejection of a ceasefire proposal. The Palestinian news agency reported 43 fatalities due to Israeli airstrikes since Friday morning, amidst ongoing shortages of food and medicine in the besieged territory. Hamas opposed any ceasefire that does not end the war and withdraw Israeli forces. The Israeli military has intensified its operations, claiming control over significant areas of Gaza. The conflict has resulted in over 51,000 deaths since its onset. The article also discusses the humanitarian crisis in Gaza, with calls for international pressure to lift the blockade and provide aid.

